From a11a24887e8e0cab828eeb7ab3295c38b8842767 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ninad Malwade <nmalwade@nvidia.com>
Date: Mon, 19 Aug 2024 15:52:55 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 35/95] NVIDIA: SAUCE: tegra: sdhci: do not apply prod settings
 during reset call

BugLink: https://bugs.launchpad.net/bugs/2080908

Do not apply general "prod" during reset call
Intermittant issues are seen and card is enumerating in HS mode
on some specific SD card due to these prod settings.

http://nvbugs/4677590
http://nvbugs/4751166
http://nvbugs/4683941
http://nvbugs/4810668

Upstream-Status: Backport
Signed-off-by: Ninad Malwade <nmalwade@nvidia.com>
Signed-off-by: Prathamesh Shete <pshete@nvidia.com>
Reviewed-by: Petlozu Pravareshwar <petlozup@nvidia.com>
Tested-by: Petlozu Pravareshwar <petlozup@nvidia.com>
Signed-off-by: Laxman Dewangan <ldewangan@nvidia.com>
Acked-by: Noah Wager <noah.wager@canonical.com>
Acked-by: Jacob Martin <jacob.martin@canonical.com>
Signed-off-by: Noah Wager <noah.wager@canonical.com>
(cherry picked from commit 061806657f31838f0144a6ffe08e6fa9cc18622c)
Signed-off-by: Matt Madison <matt@madison.systems>
---
 drivers/mmc/host/sdhci-tegra.c | 3 ---
 1 file changed, 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/mmc/host/sdhci-tegra.c b/drivers/mmc/host/sdhci-tegra.c
index aee256750196..2f55f7756a7d 100644
--- a/drivers/mmc/host/sdhci-tegra.c
+++ b/drivers/mmc/host/sdhci-tegra.c
@@ -416,9 +416,6 @@ static void tegra_sdhci_reset(struct sdhci_host *host, u8 mask)
 	if (!(mask & SDHCI_RESET_ALL))
 		return;
 
-	if (tegra_get_platform() == TEGRA_PLATFORM_SILICON)
-		tegra_sdhci_write_prod_settings(host, "prod");
-
 	tegra_sdhci_set_tap(host, tegra_host->default_tap);
 
 	misc_ctrl = sdhci_readl(host, SDHCI_TEGRA_VENDOR_MISC_CTRL);
-- 
2.43.0

